| accessdate =1 February 2008
| location =London
| archive-date =2020-03-28
| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20200328055543/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/
| dead-url =no
}}</ref> 舉辦[[白色婚禮|白色婚禮]]的傳統則要追溯到1840年[[維多利亞女王|維多利亞女王]]與[[阿爾伯特親王|阿爾伯特親王]]的婚禮，自維多利亞女王穿著白婚紗結婚之後，白色婚紗便被與純潔與奢華聯繫起來了。<ref>Otnes, Cele and Pleck, Elizabeth (2003). Cinderella Dreams: The Allure of the Lavish Wedding, p.31. University of California Press</ref><ref>Milligan, Lauren (28 April 2011) [http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/04/28/royal-wedding-dresses-from-history---queen-victoria-princess-margaret-princess-alexandra Royal Rules] Vogue. Retrieved 27 June 2011</ref>

===時裝===
[[File:Rosie_Huntington-Whiteley_C&R_11.jpg|180px]]]]

倫敦是世界時尚之都之一，[[倫敦時裝週|倫敦時裝週]]是著名的時裝週之一。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britishfashioncouncil.com/content.aspx?CategoryID=420|title=British Fashion Council website|accessdate=10 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708094732/http://www.britishfashioncouncil.com/content.aspx?CategoryID=420|archive-date=2011-07-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 此活動由[[倫敦時裝協會|倫敦時裝協會]]組織，每年二月和九月舉辦兩次。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/fashion/article-23746171-costelloe-is-head-and-shoulders-ahead-at-fashion-week.do|title=London Evening Standard article|accessdate=10 March 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100415213741/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/fashion/article-23746171-costelloe-is-head-and-shoulders-ahead-at-fashion-week.do|archivedate=2010-04-15|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 時裝週上會展出上百位設計師的作品。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.londonfashionweek.co.uk/designers.aspx?exibitor=1&PageSize=100|title=London Fashion Week website|accessdate=10 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723153102/http://www.londonfashionweek.co.uk/designers.aspx?exibitor=1&PageSize=100|archive-date=2011-07-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 此外倫敦也有許多非正式的時裝展覽活動。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artslondonnews.co.uk/20100219-fashion-week-day-1-outside|title=Arts London website|accessdate=10 March 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100224061034/http://www.artslondonnews.co.uk/20100219-fashion-week-day-1-outside|archivedate=2010-02-24|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 英國設計師[[瑪麗·匡特|瑪麗·匡特]]是“[[搖擺倫敦|搖擺倫敦]]”的重要人物之一，也是她發明了[[迷你裙|迷你裙]]和[[熱褲|熱褲]]。<ref>Ros Horton, Sally Simmons, 2007. [http://books.google.com/books?id=7LYLOj2APSsC&pg=PA170&dq=mary+quant+mini+skirt&hl=en&ei=IEcVTOOdH93GOLuepYEM&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=mary%20quant%20mini%20skirt&f=false Women Who Changed the World]</ref> 而[[查理斯·弗雷德里克·沃思|查理斯·弗雷德里克·沃思]]則被認為是[[Haute_couture|Haute couture]]之父。<ref>Jacqueline C. Kent (2003). [http://books.google.com/books?id=5EgJ9BwO5Q0C&pg=PA21&dq=charles+frederick+worth+haute+couture&hl=en&ei=mxbnS83pFJGB_QaU56WdCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=charles%20frederick%20worth%20haute%20couture&f=false Business Builders in Fashion – Charles Frederick Worth – The Father of Haute Couture] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=5EgJ9BwO5Q0C&pg=PA21&dq=charles+frederick+worth+haute+couture&hl=en&ei=mxbnS83pFJGB_QaU56WdCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=charles%20frederick%20worth%20haute%20couture&f=false |date=20160512001627 }} The Oliver Press, Inc., 2003</ref><ref>Claire B. Shaeffer (2001). [http://books.google.com/books?id=e3Sd_mikSP4C&pg=PA7&dq=charles+frederick+worth+haute+couture&hl=en&ei=mxbnS83pFJGB_QaU56WdCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CFkQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=charles%20frederick%20worth%20haute%20couture&f=false Couture sewing techniques] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=e3Sd_mikSP4C&pg=PA7&dq=charles+frederick+worth+haute+couture&hl=en&ei=mxbnS83pFJGB_QaU56WdCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CFkQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=charles%20frederick%20worth%20haute%20couture&f=false |date=20170107190023 }} "Originating in mid- 19th-century Paris with the designs of an Englishman named Charles Frederick Worth, haute couture represents an archaic tradition of creating garments by hand with painstaking care and precision". Taunton Press, 2001</ref>

而因美式英文及英式英文的分別，部分衣著的叫法不同，如美式英語中意為「長褲」的pants，在英式英語中意為「內褲」等等<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mings.mpweekly.com/mings-fashion/20180802-91540 |title=時裝冷知識：原來Fanny pack有其他意思？出國要慎用以下這些字！ |access-date=2018-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180806054748/https://mings.mpweekly.com/mings-fashion/20180802-91540 |archive-date=2018-08-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

== 交流方式==
[[File:K6_Telephone_Box_and_Edward_VII_Pillar_Box_Amberley.png|thumb]]和紅色的[[皇家郵政|皇家郵政]]信箱]]
[[紅色電話亭|紅色電話亭]]和紅色的[[皇家郵政|皇家郵政]]信箱是英國大街小巷常見的事物，已經成為了英國文化的象征。<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2479115/How-Royal-Mail-builds-Britains-iconic-letter-boxes.html#ixzz3IDFUe7u2 "From pillar to post: How Royal Mail builds Britain's letter boxes - and why they look exactly the same now as they did 160 years ago"]. Daily Mail. Retrieved 5 November 2014</ref> 紅色電話亭由[[吉爾斯·吉爾伯特·斯科特|吉爾斯·吉爾伯特·斯科特]]爵士設計於1924年，而信箱則在1850年代[[維多利亞女王|維多利亞女王]]統治時期就出現了，是1830年代[[羅蘭·希爾|羅蘭·希爾]]對英國郵政制度改革的結果。現在還在使用的信箱大多製造於1905年之後。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.bathpostalmuseum.co.uk/history-of-the-post-box.html |publisher=Bath Postal Museum |title=History of the British Postbox |accessdate=19 November 2009}}</ref>

[[賀卡|賀卡]]是一種傳統的英國祝賀方式，收發賀卡也是英國文化中重要的一個組成部份。<ref name="GCA">[http://www.greetingcardassociation.org.uk/info-resource/market-info/facts-and-figures Facts And Figures – GCA: The Greeting Card Association]. Retrieved 12 June 2011.</ref> [[情人節|情人節]]卡自18世紀末以來開始流行，并傳播到了其他國家。<ref>[http://www.emotionscards.com/museum/vals.html The History of Valentine's Day Cards] {{Wayback|url=http://www.emotionscards.com/museum/vals.html |date=20110807022738 }} Emotionscards.com. Retrieved 22 February 2010.</ref> 現在一般英國人都會花錢買情人節賀卡。<ref>[http://www.brc.org.uk/details04.asp?id=1091&kCat=&kData=1 Valentine's Day worth £1.3 Billion to UK Retailers] {{Wayback|url=http://www.brc.org.uk/details04.asp?id=1091&kCat=&kData=1 |date=20120118043542 }} [[British_Retail_Consortium|British Retail Consortium]]. Retrieved 12 June 2011.</ref> 羅蘭·希爾的改革使得郵票（[[黑便士郵票|黑便士郵票]]）開始通行，這種方法減少了郵資，使得個人間通信和郵寄賀卡成為可能。[[聖誕卡|聖誕卡]]由[[亨利·科爾|亨利·科爾]]發明於1843年，現在佔據了英國賀卡銷量的一半，每年售出的聖誕卡超過6億張。<ref name="GCA"/> 在生日、母親節、父親節以及復活節，英國人也會寄出賀卡。<ref name="GCA"/><ref>{{cite news |url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/6043426.stm |title = Card sharps |publisher = BBC News |date = 12 October 2006 |accessdate = 12 June 2011 |first = Sean |last = Coughlan |archive-date = 2016-03-12 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160312234142/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/6043426.stm |dead-url = no }}</ref>

